author: Stacy A. Anderson, Associated Press
title: Obama celebrates American music with 'eclectic bunch'
text: Photo: Susan Walsh, AP President Barack Obama walks onto the stage in the East Room of the White House in Washington at the beginning of the "In Performance at the White House" series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. This event, “A Celebration of American Creativity" will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the National Foundation on the Arts and the Humanities Act. President Barack Obama walks onto the stage in the East Room of the... WASHINGTON (AP) — Bopping his head to the beat and swaying to a blues version of "America the Beautiful," President Barack Obama on Wednesday night celebrated what he called one of the country's most precious gifts: "American creativity."
